It is often said that a data scientist spends 80% of her time wrangling data and only 20% doing actual analysis. While the actual number may vary, the fact remains that data wrangling is a critical skill in data science, and often underestimated by novices. Real-world data is messy, with missing information, corrupted values and other issues. Fortunately, Python provides us with excellent tools and libraries to handle data issues.
